# FILE: .dockerignore
# PURPOSE: Exclude files from the Docker build context.
#
# HOW IT WORKS:
#   When you run `docker build`, Docker sends every file in the project
#   folder to the Docker daemon. .dockerignore tells Docker which files
#   to exclude from that transfer entirely.
#
# NOTE: With the new Dockerfile using selective COPY (copying only specific
# PHP files and directories), most non-app files are already excluded by
# not being explicitly COPYed. But .dockerignore provides a safety net —
# if someone accidentally adds a wildcard COPY, these files are still excluded.

# ── SECRETS — NEVER in the image ──────────────────────────────
.env

# ── USER DATA — belongs on host volumes, not in image ─────────
logs/
private_uploads/

# ── PROJECT ROOT FILES — not needed in image ──────────────────
# These are deployment/infrastructure files, not app files
Dockerfile
docker-compose.yml
docker-compose.*.yml
init.sql
setup.sh
.env.example

# ── GIT ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.git/
.gitignore

# ── SYSTEM / EDITOR FILES ─────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*.swo
*.log